NAK People say that Pebble contains only low grade copper implying I suppose that it is unprofitable But all porphyry deposits are low grade There is no such thing as a high grade porphyry Escondida in Chile Bingham Canyon in Utah and Grasberg in Indonesia are all porphyry deposits and all are very profitable thank you very much The distinguishing feature of a porphyry deposit is that though the ore is low grade if you compare it with a veintype deposit like the Homestake gold mine in the Black Hills of South Dakota it is also massive The strike length at Pebble is 15 miles and within that length are contained 81 billion pounds of copper 115 million ounces of gold and 515 million ounces of gold The strike is open to the east and there are several miles to the claims boundary The amount of minerals could easily double at Pebble with further drilling of the East Graben
